 A 52-year-old old female pastor, Charity Okpara, was on Wednesday arraigned  before an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court for alleged theft of a four-month-old baby girl from her church member, Mrs blessing Okon. Okpara is facing a four-count charge bordering on conspiracy, unlawful abduction and child trafficking before Chief Magistrate Mrs Bola Osunsanmi. Prosecuting ASP Ezekiel Ayorinde told the court that Okpara committed the offences with others still at large on November 5 at No 5 Kayode Street, Ajangbadi, Okokomaiko, Lagos. ASP Ayorinde alleged that the defendant stole the four-month-old baby, Princess Oluchi, from her mother through fraudulent means. He said that all efforts made to locate the baby proved abortive. Chief Magistrate Osunsanmi, granted her bail in the sum of N200,000 with two sureties in like sum. The case continues on February 24.